id: pm-rjgh
title: "Docs hygiene: stop shipping PRD.md in npm package, dedupe PRD<->docs, slim CHANGELOG, reconcile marketplace.json"
description: Docs audit. PRD.md (118KB) is in package.json files and ships to every install while duplicating docs/ (commands/architecture/search/extensions/testing) and drifting from them; remove from published files and trim/relink it. CHANGELOG.md (71KB) is bloated by the 2026.5.3-1..8 same-day cluster; collapse to one entry. Root marketplace.json and .claude-plugin/marketplace.json have drifted (root lacks metadata/category) - reconcile from a single source (both have contract/smoke coupling). Tighten AGENTS.md to defer workflow detail to docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md. No private-infra leaks found in tracked docs (verified).
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: cleanup,docs,packaging
created_at: "2026-05-21T21:57:15.117Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T07:56:28.328Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: PRD.md not in published package; CHANGELOG slimmed; marketplace.json files reconciled with contract+smoke green; no doc drift.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "Removed PRD.md (117KB) from package.json files[] (no longer published to npm; still tracked in repo). Reconciled marketplace.json to canonical .claude-plugin/marketplace.json schema (metadata.{description,version} + plugin category 'productivity'); both files now byte-identical. CHANGELOG-slim sub-goal superseded by PR #62 (CHANGELOG fully pm-changelog-generated). AGENTS.md intentionally unchanged (already a 108-line low-context entrypoint deferring to docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md; quickstart block is injector-managed)."
expected_result: PRD.md not published; marketplace.json files reconciled with contract+smoke green; no doc drift.
actual_result: Done. npm pack dry-run confirms PRD.md gone and both marketplace files still shipped; claude-plugin-contract + smoke-claude-plugin green; check-secrets clean; full release gate green.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T07:18:19.449Z",claude-code-agent,"Coordinator scope refresh 2026-05-25: shipping this now. Validated: (1) PRD.md (117KB) is STILL in package.json files[] and ships to every npm install -> remove. (2) marketplace.json drift CONFIRMED: root uses top-level description + no plugin category; .claude-plugin/marketplace.json uses metadata.{description,version} + plugin category 'productivity'. Reconcile from single canonical source; coupling in scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs + tests/integration/claude-plugin-contract.spec.ts. (3) AGENTS.md tighten to defer workflow detail to docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md. (4) CHANGELOG-slim goal is now OBSOLETE: PR #62 made CHANGELOG.md a fully pm-changelog-generated artifact (823 items, --check passes/in-sync); manual slimming would be reverted by the generator, so dropping that sub-goal. No secret leaks found in tracked files (check-secrets clean; abs-home-paths only in synthetic test fixtures)."
  "2026-05-25T07:28:25.511Z",docs-hygiene-agent,"docs-hygiene-agent evidence (branch chore/docs-hygiene-and-item-record-cast-dedupe).\n\nITEM 1 - Stop shipping PRD.md: DONE. Removed only the \"PRD.md\" entry from package.json files[]. PRD.md remains tracked in repo (117897 bytes, still in git ls-files). Pre-check confirmed nothing requires PRD.md in the published package: the only non-docs reference is src/cli/commands/validate.ts FILE_SCAN_ROOT_FILES, which scans the repo-local PRD.md for command references and is unaffected by the npm files[] change (did NOT touch src/). No test enforces PRD.md in files[]: release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts requiredPublishFiles is a subset (dist/**, README.md, LICENSE, docs/**, packages/pm-*/**, scripts/finalize-build.mjs, install.sh, install.ps1, prepare-build-cache.mjs) and does NOT list PRD.md, so removal does not break it (verified: 32/32 pass).\n\nITEM 2 - Reconcile marketplace.json: DONE. Canonical schema decision: aligned ROOT marketplace.json to the .claude-plugin/marketplace.json shape (the canonical Claude Code marketplace shape) -> moved top-level description into metadata.{description,version:1.4.0}, reordered plugin so source follows name, added plugin category:productivity. The two files are now BYTE-IDENTICAL (diff empty). Did NOT change the contract test or smoke script: neither encodes the drift. claude-plugin-contract.spec.ts only asserts root marketplace name===pm, plugin pm-claude present, source===./plugins/pm-claude (no description/metadata/category assertions). smoke-claude-plugin.mjs only asserts .claude-plugin name===pm and plugins[0].name===pm-claude. Both pass unchanged.\n\nITEM 3 - AGENTS.md tighten: SKIPPED (not clearly safe/beneficial). AGENTS.md is already the deliberate 108-line low-context entrypoint; its Progressive Disclosure table (line 9) and When-Unsure section (line 108) ALREADY point to docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md. There is no verbatim-duplicated prose to collapse: the overlap with AGENT_GUIDE.md (147 lines) is complementary, not copied (different flag variants, AGENT_GUIDE has the fuller priority/hierarchy/plan/schema detail). The Workflow Quickstart block is wrapped in pm-cli:agent-guidance:start:v1 markers - machine-managed by pm init --agent-guidance - so pointer-replacing it would risk injector-contract drift and is out of scope. docs-skills-gate.mjs imposes NO AGENTS.md length/section constraint (AGENTS.md is not in its REQUIRED_DOC_FILES or budget map). AGENTS.md left untouched.\n\nCHANGELOG sub-goal: SUPERSEDED/OBSOLETE - confirmed not acted on. CHANGELOG.md is now a fully pm-changelog-generated artifact (PR #62); manual slimming would be reverted by the generator. Did NOT edit CHANGELOG.md.\n\nFILES CHANGED (mine only): package.json (files[] -PRD.md), marketplace.json (reconciled). Did NOT touch src/, vitest.config.ts, CHANGELOG.md, or AGENTS.md. (Other src/ edits in git status are the co-resident cast-dedupe agent's work.)\n\nVERIFICATION (exact):\n- pnpm build: green (exit 0).\n- claude-plugin-contract.spec.ts: 11/11 pass.\n- release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (asserts files[]): 32/32 pass.\n- npm pack --dry-run | grep -i prd: NO match (PRD.md gone). Both marketplace.json (root + .claude-plugin) still shipped at 1.2kB each.\n- node scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs: PASSED (31 files, 18 tools, full workflow, manifest names consistent).\n- node scripts/check-secrets.mjs: clean (No credential-like secrets detected).\n\nLeaving pm-rjgh OPEN for coordinator to close after integrated gate."
  "2026-05-25T07:56:28.308Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #65 review response (CodeRabbit, quick-win): added contract coverage in tests/integration/claude-plugin-contract.spec.ts for the reconciled manifest fields (metadata block, metadata.description string, metadata.version === plugin version, plugin category 'productivity') PLUS a new invariant test asserting root marketplace.json deepEquals .claude-plugin/marketplace.json so the two manifests can never drift again. Contract spec green (11+1 tests). Sourcery posted only a weekly diff-char rate-limit notice (no actionable review)."
close_reason: Docs/packaging hygiene shipped; PRD.md unpublished + marketplace reconciled; CHANGELOG-slim superseded by auto-gen; gate green.
